%% Reconstructed from docs/img/request_sequence.png for the Slidey overview deck.
sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  actor Client
  participant Gateway as API Gateway<br/>(middleware stack)
  participant AuthN as AuthN Resolver<br/>(+ vendor plugin → IdP)
  participant Handler as Gear Handler<br/>(api/rest, PEP entry)
  participant Domain as Domain Service
  participant PEP as PolicyEnforcer (PEP)
  participant PDP as AuthZ Resolver (PDP)<br/>(+ vendor plugin)
  participant Repo as Repository + SecureConn
  participant DB as Gear DB

  Client->>Gateway: HTTP request + Bearer token
  Note over Gateway: SetRequestId / Trace / Timeout /<br/>BodyLimit / CORS / MIME / RateLimit

  rect rgb(54, 66, 92)
    Note over Gateway,AuthN: Authentication (AuthN middleware)
    Gateway->>Gateway: resolve route auth requirement
    alt route is .authenticated()
      Gateway->>AuthN: authenticate(bearer_token)
      AuthN->>AuthN: vendor plugin validates / introspects token (IdP)
      AuthN-->>Gateway: AuthenticationResult { SecurityContext }
      Gateway->>Gateway: inject Extension SecurityContext
    else missing token
      Gateway-->>Client: 401 Unauthorized (MISSING_BEARER)
    end
    Gateway->>Gateway: ScopeEnforcement (token scopes) + License check
  end

  Gateway->>Handler: dispatch to Axum handler + SecurityContext
  Handler->>Handler: deserialize DTO / extract Path and OData query
  Handler->>Domain: service.method(&ctx, args)

  rect rgb(45, 78, 58)
    Note over Domain,PDP: Authorization (PEP → PDP)
    Domain->>PEP: access_scope(ctx, ResourceType, action, resource_id)
    PEP->>PDP: EvaluationRequest(subject, action, resource, context, token_scopes)
    PDP->>PDP: vendor plugin evaluates policies<br/>(+ tenant/RG hierarchy)
    PDP-->>PEP: decision + constraints
    alt decision = false or constraints missing
      PEP-->>Domain: EnforcerError::Denied → 403 Forbidden (fail-closed)
    else allowed
      PEP->>PEP: compile constraints → AccessScope
      PEP-->>Domain: AccessScope
    end

    Domain->>Repo: repo.op(&conn, &scope, ...)
    Repo->>Repo: secure().scope_with(&scope)<br/>SQL WHERE (tenant + constraints)
    Repo->>DB: scoped query / insert / update
    DB-->>Repo: rows (0 rows on point op → 404)
    Repo-->>Domain: domain model(s)
  end

  Domain-->>Handler: domain result or DomainError
  Handler-->>Gateway: ApiResult T -> JSON / RFC-9457 Problem
  Gateway->>Gateway: ErrorMapping (canonical errors), Trace span close
  Gateway-->>Client: HTTP response
